@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Uconec' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any tile, this will make it rotate clockwise by
90 degrees, if the open portion of the tile faces the open portion
of a neighbouring tile, both will 'connect' together, if both tiles
are of the same colour, you will get 5 points, otherwise, you will
get 1 point.

  Note that when tiles are connected, none of these can be rotated
afterwards... and avoid isolating any tile between other connected
tiles, as the game will end when there are no remaining tiles that
can be connected together...

  When you have successfully connected all tiles together, Uconec
will display a new board and the game will continue...

  Have fun!

  To quit the game, click on the game window's close button or
press the 'Esc' key.

@endnode

